{"books":{"13":{"id":"2119","title":"What I Believe","description":"<p>\"The inner working of my soul, which I wish to speak of here, was not the result of a methodical investigation of doctrinal theology, or of the actual texts of the gospel; it was a sudden removal of all that hid the true meaning of the Christian doctrine \u2013 a momentary flash of light, which made everything clear to me.  It was something like that which might happen to a man who, after vainly attempting, by a false plan, to build up a statue out of a confused heap of small pieces of marble, suddenly guesses at the figure they are intended to form by the shape of the largest piece; and then, on beginning to set up the statue, finds his guess confirmed by the harmonious joining in of the various pieces.\" (Extract from Chapter 1)<\/p>","url_text_source":"http:\/\/www.nonresistance.org\/docs_htm\/Tolstoy\/~What_I_Believe\/WIB_contents.html","language":"English","copyright_year":"1886","num_sections":"14","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/2119","url_zip_file":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/download\/whatibelieve_1101_librivox\/whatibelieve_1101_librivox_64kb_mp3.zip","url_project":"","url_librivox":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/what-i-believe-by-leo-tolstoy\/","url_other":null,"totaltime":"7:58:50","totaltimesecs":28730,"authors":[{"id":"217","first_name":"Leo","last_name":"Tolstoy","dob":"1828","dod":"1910"}],"url_iarchive":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/details\/whatibelieve_1101_librivox","sections":[{"id":"3211","section_number":"0","title":"Preface and Introduction","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"440","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"94","display_name":"David Barnes"}]},{"id":"3212","section_number":"1","title":"Chapter 1","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"1158","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"94","display_name":"David Barnes"}]},{"id":"3213","section_number":"2","title":"Chapter 2","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"855","file_name":n